      "id": "entry_1763802984_0d3c280a",
      "title": "Numbered Memory Convention",
      "content": "The Numbered Memory Convention organizes knowledge by priority for efficient loading and retrieval.\n\nNumber ranges:\n- 00-09: Core system memories (loaded first if context breaks)\n- 10-99: Primary operational memories\n- 100-199: Standards and procedures\n- 200-299: Project-specific information\n- 300-399: Tools and documentation\n- 1000+: Specialized conceptual frameworks\n\nThis allows the orchestrator to load exactly what is needed based on task type, maintaining focused context while ensuring critical knowledge is always accessible.",
