      "id": "entry_1763802984_c748ce6d",
      "title": "MonkeyBrain Documentation Standard",
      "content": "The MonkeyBrain Documentation Standard ensures knowledge remains accessible to small local models (8k context) while scaling up for larger models.\n\nCore principles:\n1. Visual-heavy documentation with emojis \n2. ELI5 (Explain Like I'm 5) approach for all concepts\n3. House/room metaphors for complex systems\n4. Clear, actionable examples\n5. Quick Start sections for immediate use\n\nPhilosophy: Be syntax-agnostic with Claude but enforce strict syntax for smaller models. If a hardcoded smolagent cannot understand it, it is too complex.",
